iSocialNetwork API

ESGI - 3A AL - 2014/2015
Open Source Rest API

Fabien GAMELIN - Ismaïl NGUYEN - Bruno VACQUEREL

GitHub > iSocialNetwork
05-26-2015

Overview

Authentication headers

In order to authenticate yourself to the service, you need to use the Authorization header for authentication and Basic Authorization (username: user ID, password: token). Each user has its own API token, allowing you to isolate access and data for each application that connects to iSocialNetwork. The header name and value are case insensitive. Should you execute the request with wrong or missing headers, you will receive an HTTP Response 401 (Unauthorized). The token and the unique user identifier are given after login or subscription.

Output format

By default settings, iSocialNetwork will return JSON format message. In case you want to the response be XML format, you need to send output field in HTTP request with you format value (eg. xml).

Example:
{
 "code": 1,
 "result": {
  "idPost": "34",
  "content": "Here an sample of json data"
  "createdDate": "2015-05-27 15:34:05"
 }
}


Output code

1 => HTTP Response 200 (OK)
2 => HTTP Response 201 (Created)
3 => HTTP Response 202 (Accepted)
4 => HTTP Response 400 (Bad Request)
5 => HTTP Response 401 (Unauthorized)
6 => HTTP Response 403 (Forbidden)
7 => HTTP Response 404 (Not Found)
8 => HTTP Response 405 (Method Not Allowed)
9 => HTTP Response 406 (Not Acceptable)
10 => HTTP Response 409 (Conflict)
11 => HTTP Response 412 (Precondition Failed)
12 => HTTP Response 417 (Expectation Failed)
13 => HTTP Response 500 (Internal Server Error)
14 => HTTP Response 501 (Not Implemented)
15 => HTTP Response 502 (Bad Gateway)
16 => HTTP Response 503 (Service Unavailable)
